      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 20040.0,
      "end_time": 22240.0,
      "text": "Sweating helps in thermoregulation."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 23200.0,
      "end_time": 28300.0,
      "text": "Thermoregulation is the process by which organisms maintain their internal body temperature."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28960.0,
      "end_time": 36660.0,
      "text": "Now, the internal body temperature of a human is about 37 degrees Celsius or 98.6 degrees Fahrenheit."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 39540.0,
      "end_time": 43340.0,
      "text": "Our enzymes and hormones work best at this temperature."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 43520.0,
      "end_time": 46380.0,
      "text": "Hence, thermoregulation is very important\nfor us."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 47540.0,
      "end_time": 52140.0,
      "text": "Well, If you ask my opinion, chocolate syrup is very important for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 52400.0,
      "end_time": 53740.0,
      "text": "Just listen."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 54840.0,
      "end_time": 61420.0,
      "text": "On a sunny day or during exercise, when our body temperature increases, our sweat glands produce sweat."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 61700.0,
      "end_time": 63940.0,
      "text": "This sweat is about 99% water."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 64400.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66040.0,
      "text": "Water is a very good heat absorbent."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 66460.0,
      "end_time": 69940.0,
      "text": "It absorbs much of our body heat and evaporates into the atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 70180.0,
      "end_time": 74060.0,
      "text": "Helping us lose heat and thus maintaining our body temperature."
